race.comment: HIGHLY INTRIGUED (4) finished fourth last time out over 1450m at Kilmore, beaten 2.75 lengths. Expecting a bold showing. CHEEKY BLINDERS (9) made considerable ground in the run home to finish third last start over 1400m at Hamilton. No reason she can't go close here from the good draw. LITTLE RICHIE TURF (8) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1600m at Bairnsdale, beaten 3.5 lengths into fifth. Looks well placed so expect a big run this time. VEGAS ON FIRE (7) was in the money two starts back at Moe but was unable to repeat the effort last time when sixth, beaten 6 lengths, at Warrnambool over 1700m. Well placed and should be about the mark.
